WHO   — The Model-Written Evals — Anthropic's 'evals' dataset (Perez et al., 2022, arXiv:2212.09251; CC-BY-4.0) — an LM writes the test questions, humans verify them, and the tests probe OTHER models for behaviors; each row {question, answer_matching_behavior, answer_not_matching_behavior}, the delta as the measure
WHAT  — Anthropic's 'evals' dataset (Perez et al., 2022, arXiv:2212.09251; CC-BY-4.0) — an LM writes the test questions, humans verify them, and the tests probe OTHER models for behaviors; each row {question, answer_matching_behavior, answer_not_matching_behavior}, the delta as the measure
WHERE — LMC · The Language of the Machine — built off Anthropic's HH-RLHF preference data  Framework inputs: chosen; rejected; the tranches; the reward model; LIMEN; the Ambassador  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the preference data's sibling, folded in: where HH-RLHF measures which answer humans prefer, the evals measure what a model will say it IS — the same delta-as-measure, turned from taste to behavior.
HOW   — Crystallized from Anthropic's HH-RLHF dataset, read through ROOT0's lens.

